# Onboarding conversations — title + no risk

## Rule

Communication inbox / right-rail monitoring titles must match the **direction of the interaction**, and onboarding threads are always **NO RISK**.

| Thread | Title | Risk badge |
|---|---|---|
| Vendor verification / preferred network invite | **Vendor onboarding** | **NO RISK** (`low`) |
| Vendor verification form submitted (same thread) | **Vendor onboarding** | **NO RISK** (`low`) |
| Local vendor-setup / intake monitoring detail | **Vendor onboarding** | **NO RISK** (`low`) |
| Tenant activation welcome / SMS consent thread | **Tenant onboarding** | **NO RISK** (`low`) |
| Active work-order or maintenance SMS | Normal heuristics | Normal risk heuristics |

## Meaning

- Onboarding invites are informational. They are not urgent maintenance or resident issues.
- Do **not** let message heuristics mis-label these threads (e.g. “Plumbing” in Flex Plumbing → plumbing issue; “repair” in the tenant welcome SMS → maintenance request).
- Title and subtitle must say vendor/tenant **onboarding**; risk stays **NO RISK**.
- When a vendor submits verification, the **same thread** gains an inbound response (see `vendor-verification-inbox-response.mdc`) — title/risk stay onboarding / no risk.

## Implementation

- `deriveRisk` / `buildTitle` / `buildSubtitle` in `src/lib/conversationMonitoring.ts` short-circuit onboarding invite **and** verification-submit copy before status/urgency/issue heuristics.
- `buildVendorSetupMonitoringDetail` in `src/lib/vendorSetupConversation.ts` uses the same vendor onboarding title + NO RISK badge.
- Detect tenant activation via welcome/consent copy (`Reply YES to get updates…`, reach-us-by-text welcome, opt-in confirmation).
- When adding new invite or onboarding monitoring surfaces, reuse this labeling.
